ANTHRAX - ARGENTINA (03): (BUENOS AIRES) COWS
*********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 13 Dec 2021
From: Ramon Noseda <rnoseda@laboratorioazul.com.ar>


There have been a number of sporadic bovine deaths but with a defined cause in a ranch in Partido de Saladillo, Province of Buenos Aires.

On [Thu 9 Dec 2021] following the submission of a metatarsal bone _Bacillus anthracis_ was cultivated [and anthrax confirmed]. The animals had been vaccinated earlier in the year during March [2021]. There were no human cases. The infected carcasses were burnt and the remains were buried along with chemical disinfectants.

The area concerned has previously seen many bovine anthrax outbreaks. Since 2014 the number of outbreaks of anthrax in this Control & Surveillance Area in the Province of Buenos Aires, 1977-2020, are much diminished. During 2002-2006, there were 93 outbreaks and in the last 4 years, 2017-2021 there have only been 3 outbreaks. This supports the success of the application of the law '6703/61 Decreto:66/63 y la Resolucion 115/14' that imposes restrictions on the movements of unvaccinated livestock in the province.

In addition, the production of anthrax vaccine in the last 3 years has been 21 to 29 million doses in the expectation of eventual eradication of this zoonotic agent.

--
Ramon Noseda
Laboratorio Azul Diagnostico S.A.
Av. 25 de Mayo 479
7300 Azul, Buenos Aires
Argentina
<rnoseda@laboratorioazul.com.ar>

[As in the US Dakota states the Argentine veterinary services are succeeding in significantly reducing the incidence of this disease. Eradication is on the horizon and they are to be congratulated for their hard work. Anthrax vaccines, just like the normal infection antibodies, have a limited life and effectiveness. As a rule of thumb, they are good for 6-9 months of protection. With the onset of summer hot temperatures, there is a reduction in immune resistance to infection and so breakthroughs will happen, which is why one must be alert for unexpected bovine deaths.

For a map of Argentina showing the location of this "Partido" (county), go to: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saladillo,_Buenos_Aires. - Mod.MHJ

ProMED map:
